Here's the step-by-step solution:

\[
\begin{align*}
a^{2} ( a^{2} - 9a - 36 ) &= a^{2} \cdot a^{2} + a^{2} \cdot (-9a) + a^{2} \cdot (-36) \\
&= a^{2+2} - 9a^{2+1} - 36a^{2} \\
&= a^{4} - 9a^{3} - 36a^{2}
\end{align*}
\]

**Final Answer:**
\[
\boxed{a^{4} - 9a^{3} - 36a^{2}}
\]

